In case of the dyad-CQDs (or NCQDs) nanocomposite systems, two lifetimes, one in nanosecond order and the other in picoseconds were observed (Fig. 3
                        , Table 1
                        ). On comparing with the data observed in the cases of dyad-gold nanocomposites [1], the former species appears to be responsible for trans isomer having longer lifetime of ns order and the later ones for folded conformation “cis” possessing relatively faster components of ps order. It is to be pointed out that the lifetimes observed in the case of dyad-CQD or dyad-NCQD are significantly larger in magnitudes than the corresponding values observed in the cases of dyad-gold systems [1]. It may be inferred that in cases of carbon quantum dots nanocomposites the environment favors both the redox centers donor and acceptor of the dyad to interact more strongly.
